description:
&lt;p&gt;East London NHS Foundation Trust (ELFT) is seeking for an enthusiastic and proactive pharmacist to develop as Community Health Service (CHS) Clinical Pharmacist working as part of the multidisciplinary Team in Community Health Services, Newham and pharmacy team in East London NHS Foundation Trust. Our pharmacy team is an enthusiastic, motivated and committed group of professionals, and we are looking for a like-minded individual to join us. We set ourselves the mission of delivering highest care and expertise in our clinical services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be self-motivated, able to work independently and above all will be passionate about providing the highest standards of care and treatment to patients in community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a multidisciplinary team to manage medicines on transfer of care and systems for safer prescribing. Experience in hospital practice would be an advantage but is not essential if the applicant is clinically up-to-date and understands the process of a full medication review and medicines reconciliation following a transfer between care settings, primarily upon transfers between hospitals as well as discharge from hospital to patients homes or care homes. You should be able to resolve issues identified and communicate effectively with service users, community health staff, other care staff, hospital staff, and GPs as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also contribute to quality improvement and clinical audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, it will be great if you have an independent prescribing qualification or will be willing to work towards that. Mentorship will be provided by our Lead Pharmacist, Newham CHS and by the wider ELFT pharmacy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent written and verbal communication skills and experience of influencing others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this role appeals to you and you have the qualities we are looking for then please get on with the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCharity OkoliEmail addresscharity.okoli@nhs.netTelephone number07741295817&lt;/p&gt;
